===Verb===
{{en-verb|accru}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To increase, to [[augment]]; to come to by way of increase; to [[arise]] or spring as a growth or result; to be added as increase, profit, or damage, especially as the [[produce]] of money [[lent]].
#* '''1590''', [[w:Edmund Spenser|Edmund Spenser]], ''The Faerie Queene''
#*: And though pow'r fail'd, her Courage did '''accrue'''
#* ''Interest '''accrues''' to principal'' - {{rfdatek|Abbott}}
#* ''The great and essential advantages '''accruing''' to society from the freedom of the press'' - {{rfdatek|Junius}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|accounting}} To be [[incurred]] as a result of the passage of time.
#: ''The monthly financial statements show all the actual but only some of the '''accrued''' expenses.''
# {{lb|en|transitive}} to [[accumulate]]
#: ''He has '''accrued''' nine sick days.''
# {{lb|en|intransitive|legal}} To become an enforceable and permanent right.

